<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7639> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7639" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. Africa 105. In MRR 1.556, delete the gentilicium Annius. Bellienus is well attested as such (Cic. Fam. 16.22.2; 8.15.2; Phil. 2.91; see Shackleton Bailey, CLF 1.489; Wiseman, NM 217, no. 66).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3532> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3532" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sall. Iug. 104.1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3531> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3531" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "For the gentile name of Bellienus, see RE s. v. \"Annius\" no. 35, no C. Annius Bellienus, Legate of Fonteius in Gaul (Cic. Font. 18). Bellienus was probably the regular governor in Africa." .
